h2 Mixins

h3 Size 
p 
  | To quickly and easily determine the size of an element, you can use the mixin 
  code size($width, $height: $width)
  |  .
h6 Usage
pre
  code.scss
    header SCSS
    p
      = 'div1 {'
      br
      = '  @include size(50px);'
      br
      = '}'
      br
      = 'div2 {'
      br
      = '  @include size(100px, 20px);'
      br
      = '}'
      br
      br
h6 Output
pre
  code.css
    header CSS
    p
      = 'div1 {'
      br
      = '  width: 50px;'
      br
      = '  height: 50px;'
      br
      = '}'
      br
      = 'div2 {'
      br
      = ' width: 100px;'
      br
      = ' height: 20px;'
      br
      = '}'

h3 Positioning 
p
  | To quickly and easily position Elemnte you can use the mixins 
  code absolute($args)
  | , 
  code fixed($args)
  | and 
  code relative($args)
  |  .
p 
  | in $args you can indicate all offsets, for example,
  code left 1em top 1.5em
  |  or 
  code top 5px right 10px bottom 15px left 10px
  | .

h3 Fontsizes in Rem
p 
  | With the
  code font-size-rem($size)
  |  and 
  code line-height-rem($size)
  |  mixins you can easily convert px in rem to have even px value given to a fallback.

h3 Background images
p 
  | Retina backgroud images make us more problems. With muffins that is no longer a problem. The Mixin 
  code background-image($name, $size:false)
  | helps you easily integrate retina wallpapers.
p 
  | In the "_helper.scss" in the "config" folder you can see your image file path
  code $image-path
  | ) ,  your file extension(
  code $image-extension
  | ) uand your retina suffix (
  code $retina-suffix
  | ) to configure.
